1. Create new Virtual Network within a new resource group. Name/ region/ IP addresses/ and create 2 separate subnets.
2. Deploy the public web server VM.
3. Ensure public web server is connected to subnet specific to public traffic.
4. Download Private key for VM.
5. Deploy private database server VM.
6. Use existing key for this VM as well.
7. Allow only SSH Port 22 traffic to this VM.
8. Make sure the private subnet created for Database vm has no public IP.
9. Validate connectivity between servers by getting the private ip address of the database server.
10. Open terminal and SSH into web server. Use log in credentials and key you downloaded to device.
11. From inside the web server, try to ping the database server. 
12. Once replies are seen, stop the ping.
13. Configure the NSG of database VM by creating a new inbound rule allowing all traffic from the web server.
